The paper discusses the property of secrecy in a protocol, which is a fundamental topic in cryptography and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions functions to estimate the security of messages, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the growth of the protocol, which could be related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses relaxed conditions to prove correctness, which could be related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
